==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lecythis
<hw>Lec"y*this</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧s"⟦icr⟧*th⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. 3 an oil flask.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus
of gigantic trees, chiefly Brazilian, of the order
<ord>Myrtace⟦ae⟧</ord>, having woody capsules opening by an apical lid.
<spn>Lecythis Zabucajo</spn> yields the delicious sapucaia nuts.
<spn>Lecythis Ollaria</spn> produces the monkey-pots, its capsules. Its
bark separates into thin sheets, like paper, used by the natives for
cigarette wrappers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Led</ent>⟦br⟧
